        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 30 at 3:18PM EDT by NWS Peachtree City GA</headline>
        <description>At 317 PM EDT, National Weather Service doppler radar indicated a
strong thunderstorm over White Plains, or 11 miles southeast of
Greensboro, moving east at 50 mph.

HAZARD...40 to 50 mph wind, pea sized hail, frequent cloud to ground
lightning and increased chance of a brief tornado.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...While winds should result in minor damage to tree limbs and
blowing around of light, unsecured objects, this storm has
also exhibited localized rotation. A brief tornado could
quickly form.

Locations impacted include...
Warrenton, White Plains, Siloam, Norwood, Camak, Springfield,
Powelton, Beall Springs, and Mayfield.
</description>
        <instruction>People outdoors should seek shelter immediately.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 800 PM EDT for
east central Georgia.</instruction>
